#: ../../manual/rigging/introduction.rst:4
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "简介"

#: ../../manual/rigging/introduction.rst:6
msgid "Rigging is a general term used for adding controls to objects, typically for the purpose of animation."
msgstr "绑定是通常用于向物体添加控件的通用术语，通常用于动画。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/introduction.rst:9
msgid "Rigging often involves using one or more of the following features:"
msgstr "绑定经常涉及使用到以下一个或多个功能："

#: ../../manual/rigging/introduction.rst:11
msgid ":ref:`Armatures <armatures-index>`"
msgstr ":ref:`骨架 <armatures-index>`"

#: ../../manual/rigging/introduction.rst:12
msgid "This allows mesh objects to have flexible joints and is often used for skeletal animation."
msgstr "这允许网格物体象具有柔性的关节，经常用于骨骼动画。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/introduction.rst:13
msgid ":ref:`Constraints <constraints-index>`"
msgstr ":ref:`约束 <constraints-index>`"

#: ../../manual/rigging/introduction.rst:14
msgid "To control the kinds of motions that make sense and add functionality to the rig."
msgstr "控制各种有意义的运动类型并为绑定添加功能。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/introduction.rst:15
msgid ":ref:`Object Modifiers <modifiers-index>`"
msgstr ":ref:`物体修改器 <modifiers-index>`"

#: ../../manual/rigging/introduction.rst:16
msgid "Mesh deformation can be quite involved, there are multiple modifiers that help control this."
msgstr "网格形变可以相当复杂，有多个修改器可以帮助控制复杂度。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/introduction.rst:17
msgid ":ref:`Shape Keys <animation-shape_keys-index>`"
msgstr ":ref:`形变关键帧 <animation-shape_keys-index>`"

#: ../../manual/rigging/introduction.rst:18
msgid "To support different target shapes *(such as facial expressions)* to be controlled."
msgstr "支持不同的目标形状 *（如面部表情）* 进行控制。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/introduction.rst:21
msgid ":ref:`Drivers <animation-drivers-index>`"
msgstr ":ref:`驱动器 <animation-drivers-index>`"

#: ../../manual/rigging/introduction.rst:20
msgid "So your rig can control many different values at once, as well as making some properties automatically update based on changes elsewhere."
msgstr "因此，你的绑定可以一次控制许多不同的值，并根据其他地方的变化自动更新一些属性。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/introduction.rst:23
msgid "Rigging can be as advanced as your project requires, rigs are effectively defining own user interface for the animator to use, without having to be concerned the underlying mechanisms."
msgstr "绑定可以像你的项目所要求的那样先进, 绑定有效地定义自己的用户界面用于动画师使用 , 而不必担心基础机制。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/introduction.rst:31
msgid "Examples"
msgstr "示例"

#: ../../manual/rigging/introduction.rst:33
msgid "An armature is often used with a modifier to deform a mesh for character animation."
msgstr "骨架通常与修改器一起用于角色动画变形网格。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/introduction.rst:34
msgid ""
"A camera rig can be used instead of animating the camera object directly to simulate real-world camera rigs *(with a boom arm, mounted on a rotating pedestal for example, effects such as camera jitter "
"can be added too).*"
msgstr "可以使用摄像机绑定来代替动画摄像机物体来直接模拟真实世界的摄像机装备 *（例如，悬臂装在旋转底座上，也可以添加摄像机抖动等效果）。*"

#: ../../manual/rigging/introduction.rst:41
msgid ""
"The content of this chapter is simply a reference to how rigging is accomplished in Blender. It should be paired with additional resources such as Nathan Vegdahl's excellent (and free!) introduction to "
"the fundamental concepts of character rigging, `Humane Rigging <https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL3wFcRXImVPOQpi-wi7uriXBkykXVUntv>`__."
msgstr ""
"本章的内容是如何在Blender中完成绑定的简单的一个参考。应该搭配额外的资源，如Nathan Vegdahl优秀（免费！）的介绍角色绑定的基本概念， `人体绑定教程 <https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL3wFcRXImVPOQpi-"
"wi7uriXBkykXVUntv>`__。"

